description: A study published in Nature Communications predicts the Arctic Ocean could face its first ice-free day as early as 2027, marking a critical environmental milestone. Conducted using 11 climate models and 366 simulations, the research highlights the urgent need for emission reductions. The loss of sea ice in the Arctic exacerbates global warming through the albedo effect, and the region is already warming four times faster than the global average.
title: Arctic Ocean Likely to Experience Ice-Free Day by 2027, Study Warns

description: Recent research published in Nature Astronomy challenges past ideas about Venus, suggesting it never had oceans or conditions for life. Analysis of the planet's volcanic gases and atmospheric composition revealed that Venus’s interior is dry, ruling out the presence of liquid water. This conclusion highlights the stark contrast between Venus and Earth, and upcoming missions from NASA and ESA aim to further explore the planet’s history
title: Study Finds Venus Likely Never Had Oceans, Challenging Past Theories

description: A study published in Royal Society Open Science explores how changes in ocean density influence marine plankton, particularly the foraminifera species Trilobatus trilobus, in incorporating carbon into their shells. These organisms play a key role in the carbon cycle by sequestering carbon in the ocean floor after death. The study, led by Dr Stergios Zarkogiannis from the University of Oxford, reveals that melting ice sheets and freshwater influx reduce ocean density, impacting plankton's calcification process.
title: Plankton’s Ability To Sequester Carbon Is Influenced by Ocean Density, Study Shows

description: The International Space Station (ISS) is set for a controlled deorbit in 2031, with plans to disintegrate over the South Pacific's remote Point Nemo. While NASA’s approach aims to reduce risks, concerns have been raised about the environmental impacts. Researchers highlight potential effects on Earth’s upper atmosphere, which remain poorly understood. Greenpeace and advocacy groups like Ocean Conservancy are also concerned about the use of oceans as dumping grounds for space debris.
title: Environmental Impact of ISS Deorbit in 2031 Raises Concerns on Oceans and Atmosphere

description: A study led by the University at Buffalo suggests primordial black holes (PBHs), formed in the early universe, could leave traces in both cosmic and terrestrial objects. Researchers believe PBHs, which are much smaller than stellar black holes, might leave hollow structures in celestial bodies like asteroids or moons. Additionally, passing through solid materials, PBHs may create microscopic tunnels, visible under a microscope.
title: Researchers Propose Evidence of Primordial Black Holes in Cosmic Objects and Earthly Materials

description: NASA astronaut Sunita Williams is leading a space farming experiment aboard the International Space Station (ISS), aimed at advancing agricultural techniques for both space and Earth. The experiment, part of NASA’s Plant Habitat-07 study, involves cultivating “Outredgeous” romaine lettuce in microgravity to examine how water availability affects plant growth. The goal is to develop sustainable food production methods for long-duration space missions, reducing dependency on resupply missions.
title: NASA’s Astronaut Sunita Williams Grows Lettuce in Space: Everything You Need to Know

description: Bitcoin soared above $100,000 for the first time on Thursday, in a significant milestone for digital assets around the world. Investors are anticipate a US administration amenable to cryptocurrencies, buoyed by US President-elect Donald Trump's apparent embrace of digital assets. The cryptocurrency market's total value has nearly doubled this year, reaching a record high of over $3.8 trillion, according to CoinGecko.
title: Bitcoin Storms Above $100,000 as Bets on US President-Elect Donald Trump Fuel Crypto Euphoria

description: Developer Polyphony Digital has announced My First Gran Turismo, a free-to-play GT experience to help introduce new players to the series. The bite-sized racing sim experience arrives on PS4 and PS5 on December 6.
title: My First Gran Turismo, a Free-to-Play Racing Sim Experience for PS4 and PS5, Arrives December 6

description: Google DeepMind unveiled the successor to the Genie artificial intelligence (AI) model, which could generate endless 2D game worlds, on Wednesday. Dubbed Genie 2, the new AI model is capable of generating unique action-controllable, playable 3D environments based on a single image prompt. The company said these generated worlds could be played by humans or can be used to train AI agents.
title: Google DeepMind Unveils Genie 2 AI Model, Can Generate Playable 3D Worlds to Train AI Agents

description: Intel's interim co-CEO David Zinsner said that the company's next chief executive officer will have manufacturing expertise as well as experience in the product side of the chipmaking business. The firm has reportedly started evaluating a handful of outsiders including former board member Lip-Bu Tan to take the reins of the struggling chipmaker, a day after the company announced the resignation of CEO Pat Gelsinger.
title: Intel's Interim Co-CEO David Zinsner Says New Chief Executive Will Have Foundry Experience

description: Moto G35 5G is set to launch in India on December 10 and will go on sale via Flipkart. As the launch date nears, the Lenovo-owned brand has hinted at the price range of the new Moto G series smartphone. The Moto G35 was unveiled in select global markets in August this year. It runs on a Unisoc T760 chipset and a 6.7-inch display. The Moto G35 carries a 50-megapixel dual rear camera unit.
title: Moto G35 5G India Price Range Revealed Ahead of Launch Next Week

description: Apple plans to invest $1 billion in a manufacturing plant in Indonesia that produces components for the company's handsets and other devices, according to the country's investment minister. Details of the investment were still being ironed out, investment minister Rosan Roeslani told reporters on Thursday.
title: Apple Plans $1 Billion Manufacturing Plant Investment in Indonesia, Minister Says

description: Portronics Beem 500 smart LED projector was launched in India on Thursday. It comes with a 1080p Full-HD native resolution and support for up to 8K Ultra-HD where supported. The projector arrives with pre-loaded OTT apps like Hotstar, Netflix, Prime Video, and YouTube. It can project up to a 120-inch display and is equipped with inbuilt 16W speakers.
title: Portronics Beem 500 Smart LED Projector With 6700 Lumens Brightness Launched in India: Price, Specifications

description: A study published in the European Journal of Archaeology proposes that slate plaques from the Late Neolithic and Copper Age Iberian Peninsula (3200–2200 BC) served as non-verbal genealogical records. The plaques, found in tombs across Portugal and Spain, were engraved with intricate geometric patterns and may have indicated clan affiliations and ancestral lineage. Research led by Prof. Katina Lillios suggests these plaques were likely used by elites, possibly to manage marriage alliances, property and burial rights.
title: Study Suggests Iberian Slate Plaques May Have Served as Non-Verbal Genealogical Records

description: Boult has introduced three new audio products in India including the Bassbox X625, Bassbox X30, and PartyBox X80. The Boult Bassbox X625 and X30 are claimed to offer 625W and 30W rated output, respectively. The Boult PartyBox X80, on the other hand, is said to provide a bass-boosted 80W-rated output.
title: Boult Bassbox X625, Bassbox X30, and PartyBox X80 Launched in India: Price, Features

description: Google has introduced a new feature for its Photos app that aims to make deleting backed-up photos and videos easier. It was reportedly first spotted in June, with code strings of the Google Photos app hinting at a feature with similar functionality. The feature, dubbed ‘Undo Device Backup’, lets users remove media from the cloud storage space offered by Google without affecting their presence on the local storage on a particular device.
title: Google Photos Rolls Out ‘Undo Device Backup’ Feature0 for Better Cloud Storage Management

description: Apple Intelligence, the company’s in-house suite of artificial intelligence (AI) features for its devices, will reportedly be provided by Baidu’s AI models in China. The Cupertino-based tech giant has so far not released its new AI features in the European Union countries and China due to regulatory obstacles. While the problem in the EU largely revolves around user privacy and interoperability concerns, in China only the AI models that are approved by the government are permitted to operate.
title: Apple Intelligence in China Will Reportedly Be Backed by Baidu’s Ernie 4.0 AI Model

description: Apple is believed to update the iPad Pro next year with a new generation chip. Most recently, Apple analyst Ming-Chi Kuo claims that the iPad Pro powered by an unannounced M5 chip will become available to customers in the fall of 2025. Apple has historically updated its iPad Pro line about every 18 months. The last generation iPad Pro (2022) models with the Apple M2 processor were launched in October 2022.
title: Apple's Next iPad Pro With M5 Chip to Enter Mass Production in Second Half of 2025: Ming-Chi Kuo

description: OnePlus 13 was unveiled in China in October with a Snapdragon 8 Elite SoC and a Hasselblad-backed 50-megapixel triple rear camera unit. The handset has been confirmed to launch in global markets outside China, including in India in January. Ahead of its launch in India, the OnePlus 13's availability details have now been confirmed.
title: OnePlus 13 Amazon Availability in India Confirmed Ahead of Launch

description: On December 4, 2024, SpaceX’s Falcon 9 rocket made history by completing its 24th mission, a new record for the company. The rocket, launched from Cape Canaveral, successfully carried 24 Starlink satellites into low Earth orbit. The first stage of the rocket also achieved its 24th successful landing, marking another significant milestone in SpaceX's reusable rocket programme.
title: SpaceX Falcon 9 Successfully Deploys 24 Starlink Satellites

description: MSI Claw 8+ AI and MSI Claw 7+ AI have been launched with Intel Core Ultra (Series 2) processors and 32GB of RAM. These devices sport up to 8-inch touchscreen displays with a 120Hz refresh rate and pack 6-cell Li-Po batteries that can be charged at 65W using a USB PD 3.0 adapter.
title: MSI Claw 8 AI+, Claw 7 AI+ With Intel Lunar Lake CPUs , Up to 8-Inch Displays Launched: Price, Specifications

description: OnePlus Ace 5 will be introduced in China this month alongside OnePlus Ace 5 Pro. As we wait for the formal announcement, the OnePlus Ace 5 Pro has reportedly received a certification from the China Compulsory Certification (CCC aka 3C) authority. The alleged listing suggests fast charging details of the phone.
title: OnePlus Ace 5 Pro Reportedly Spotted on China’s 3C Site With 100W Fast Charging Support

description: NASA’s PREFIRE mission, launched in 2024, is utilizing CubeSats to capture groundbreaking data on far-infrared radiation emitted from polar regions. These measurements, which track heat escaping from the Arctic and Antarctic, provide critical insights into Earth’s energy balance, a key component in understanding climate change. Despite encountering technical challenges with GPS units, the CubeSats successfully began transmitting data in mid-2024. The first data products were made available in October 2024, marking the first systematic quantification of far-infrared radiation from the poles. This data is expected to improve climate models and predictions about the impact of global warming on ice, oceans, and weather patterns. Further data releases are anticipated in early 2025
title: NASA's Twin Mini Satellites Captures Far-Infrared Radiation from Polar Regions

description: One UI 7 is Samsung's Android 15-based operating system (OS) that was unveiled at the Samsung Developer Conference (SDC) 2024 last month. At the time, Samsung confirmed that it would be released in early access for Galaxy devices later this year but did not reveal a definite timeline. A tipster now suggests that the One UI 7 Beta will be rolled out today (December 5) globally and the Samsung Galaxy S24 series could be one of the first devices to get it.
title: One UI 7 Beta Said to Roll Out on December 5; Galaxy S24 Series Said to Get Priority Access

description: Google introduced its weather predicting artificial intelligence (AI) model GenCast on Wednesday. The AI model was developed by the Mountain View-based tech giant’s AI research division Google DeepMind. The company’s researchers have also published a paper on the technology highlighting its capabilities in making medium-range weather forecasts. The company claims that the system was able to outperform existing state-of-the-art forecasting models in terms of resolution and accuracy.
title: Google’s AI-Powered Weather Prediction Model GenCast Outperforms Top Forecasting Systems, Says Study

description: Netflix presents The Roshans, a docu-series chronicling the story of Bollywood’s Roshan family. Spanning three generations, the series delves into the contributions of Roshan Lal Nagrath, Rakesh Roshan, Rajesh Roshan and Hrithik Roshan. Directed by Shashi Ranjan, it features insights from family members and industry colleagues. This intimate portrayal of the Roshan dynasty highlights their indelible impact on Indian cinema and music.
title: The Roshans OTT Release Date: When and Where to Watch it Online?

description: Xiaomi Pad 7 was launched in China in October alongside the Xiaomi Pad 7 Pro. Since its launch in China, global variants of the tablet have been spotted on several certification sites. The Indian variant of the Xiaomi Pad 7 has previously appeared on the Bureau of Indian Standards (BIS) website. Now, the purported variant has been listed on Geekbench.

ColorOS 15 brings Android 15 to Oppo devices and carries enhanced visual elements texture interpretation, detailed animations, and new themes.

description: Samsung's Galaxy tri-fold phone has been in the rumour mill for quite some time now. The foldable with three screens and two hinges is considered the South Korean brand's next big bet after the success of its foldable devices. No concrete information is available about the triple-folding smartphone, but DSCC analyst Ross Young suggests that it is being prepared for a 2026 launch.
title: Samsung's First Galaxy Tri-Fold Smartphone to Launch in Early 2026: Ross Young

description: OnePlus has unveiled a new initiative called Project Starlight, committing to invest Rs. 6,000 crore in India over the coming three years. The investment aims to enhance customer service and device durability, building on the company's existing repair program for smartphones with display issues. OnePlus also says it plans to introduce new features specifically designed for Indian users.
title: OnePlus Announces Project Starlight Initiative With Rs. 6,000 Crore Investment in India

description: The Tamil movie Sir, directed by Bose Venkat and starring Vemal, is set for its OTT release on Aha. Known for addressing societal issues through a compelling storyline, Sir follows a family of teachers fighting caste-based discrimination to bring education to their village. While the exact release date remains unconfirmed, reports indicate it could premiere on 6 December 2024. The film is produced by Grass Root Film Company, with music by Siddhu Kumar and cinematography by Iniyan J. Harish.
title: Sir OTT Release Date: Tamil Action Drama Film Set to Stream on Aha Soon

description: Pushpa 2: The Rule, featuring Allu Arjun and Rashmika Mandanna, was released in cinemas on December 5, 2024. Directed by Sukumar, the film continues the gripping story of Pushpa Raj's ascent in the smuggling underworld. The movie has been praised for its powerful performances, compelling narrative, and stunning visuals. Netflix is reportedly set to stream the movie post its theatrical run. Fans can expect its digital release announcement soon. With a stellar cast including Fahadh Faasil, Jagapathi Babu, and Anasuya Bharadwaj, the sequel is making waves in the industry
title: Pushpa 2 OTT Release: Allu Arjun's Action Drama Expected to Stream on Netflix

description: The Sundance award-winning Girls Will Be Girls, directed by Shuchi Talati, will stream on Amazon Prime Video starting December 18, 2024. Starring Kani Kusruti and Preeti Panigrahi, the coming-of-age drama delves into the complexities of adolescence and familial relationships. Recognised for its compelling narrative, the film received critical acclaim at Sundance, winning the Audience Award in the World Cinema Dramatic category
title: Girls Will Be Girls OTT Release Date: When and Where to Watch it Online?

description: Jaaved Jaaferi’s much-awaited crime drama Mohrey is set to release on MX Player. The series follows the intertwined lives of Michael, an informant within the police force, and Arjun, an undercover officer trying to break into the criminal empire of gangster Bosco Salvador. The trailer has already piqued interest, showcasing a high-stakes narrative filled with betrayal, loyalty, and rivalry. With Jaaved Jaaferi leading the cast, alongside Neeraj Kabi, Gayatri Bhardwaj, and Aashim Gulati, Mohrey promises to be a gripping watch. Directed by Mukul Abhyankar, the show explores the dangerous underworld of Mumbai, setting the stage for intense conflicts and dramatic turns. Audiences can catch the full series on MX Player starting December 6
title: Mohrey OTT Release Date: Watch Jaaved Jaaferi’s Crime Thriller on Amazon MX Player

These newly launched headsets come with an environmental noise cancellation (ENC) supported quad-mic system as well.
title: Lava Probuds T24 With Up to 45 Hours Total Battery Life Launched in India: Price, Specifications

description: ESA’s Proba-3 mission, aimed at studying the Sun’s corona through an artificial eclipse, has been rescheduled to December 5, 2024, following a technical delay. The mission, which will launch aboard India’s Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle (PSLV), will use two satellites to demonstrate advanced formation-flying technology. These satellites will align with millimetre precision to create a controlled eclipse, allowing for prolonged observations of the Sun’s outer atmosphere.
title: ISRO Delays PSLV Launch That Will Carry ESA’s Proba-3 to Space, to Take Place on December 5

title: Activision Announces Call of Duty: Black Ops 6 Free Trial Week From December 13
